{
  "texts": [
    "A striking finding is the significant drop in accuracy when predicting on images of darker skin tones (FST V-VI).",
    "This aligns with the literature of both special and general purpose models performing worse on darker tones [14], and provides an avenue for significant improvement.",
    "Furthermore, the comparison with board-certified dermatologists reveals a nuanced picture of GPT-4V's role in healthcare.",
    "In contrast to the study by Buckley et.",
    "al [16], we show that human experts in the form of dermatologists significantly outperform GPT-4V on accurately predicting malignancy with p<0.05."
  ]
}